n by examining their imagined relationship to the rural through sound, shedding new light on the urgent issues of migration and belonging.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aForeign workers, MoroccanzItalyzUmbria. 0aMasculinity in music. 0aMoroccanszItalyzUmbriaxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aMusiczMoroccoxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  amigration, rurality, masculinity, Morocco, Italy, ?awt l-?arubiya, ?arubiya, ?ai?a, ?abidat r-rma, sha?bi.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226818689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226818689/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099281-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPKb2022